{"sequence":75,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T01:36:15.276683204Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-635ab8d4","body":"finding_summary: `ProcessBackendAdapter` and `TmuxAdapter` still pass an empty stdout string into `classify_exit_failure_with_output()` whenever `extract_stdout_error()` returns `None`, so backends that print exhaustion text only to plain stdout are still classified as `TransportFailure` and retried instead of degrading. severity: high affected_files: [\"src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1562-1585\", \"src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1626-1638\", \"src/adapters/tmux.rs:632-646\"] remediation_hint: When there is no structured stdout error, pass a bounded plain-text stdout tail into the classifier in both the normal path and the retry-without-resume path.","dedup_key":"02f1afd274a45e76f633fc371d407e064873b6abaf03878e4d1f0d9811f4cd12","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260414001056","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":76,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T01:36:15.285198527Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-c3dbda29","body":"finding_summary: The exhaustion matcher still misses common plain-text quota wording such as `insufficient credits`; `BACKEND_EXHAUSTED_PATTERNS` only matches narrower phrases like `credits exhausted`, `credits depleted`, `purchase more credits`, and `insufficient_quota`. severity: medium affected_files: [\"src/adapters/process_backend.rs:1942-1952\"] remediation_hint: Broaden the plain-text exhaustion patterns used for stdout/stderr classification to cover unstructured credit-insufficiency wording without weakening the existing transient-rate-limit safeguards.","dedup_key":"03c79fefdaf0b3e88a56f8dfa2afe7760fe473c861db3bdbb8490a70c098c3d4","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260414001056","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":77,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T01:36:15.293633941Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-93e191ce","body":"finding_summary: Regression coverage for stdout-only exhaustion classification is still missing. The process-backend tests cover structured stdout JSON and stderr fallback, but not a plain-text stdout-only exhaustion case, and the tmux adapter tests contain no failure-classification coverage for this path. severity: medium affected_files: [\"tests/unit/process_backend_test.rs:2131-2200\", \"tests/unit/tmux_adapter_test.rs:1-626\"] remediation_hint: Add adapter-level tests where stderr is empty and stdout contains a plain-text exhaustion message, then assert `BackendExhausted` so graceful degradation avoids retries.","dedup_key":"375daf1710daa9922a392ed9fbb61301be0468f4e5d90229089d50e9241470f1","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260414001056","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":78,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T01:36:15.302037855Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-237ad494","body":"The core implementation for the bead is completely missing. No source files have been modified (verified via git diff and git status). Both call sites — process_backend.rs:1633 and tmux.rs:638 — still use `stdout_error.as_deref().unwrap_or_default()` which falls back to an empty string when `extract_stdout_error()` returns `None`. This means stdout-only exhaustion messages (e.g., \"You've hit your usage limit\" printed to stdout without a structured JSON envelope) are still classified as TransportFailure instead of BackendExhausted.\n\nAll five acceptance criteria are unmet:\n1. Backends printing exhaustion messages only to stdout are NOT classified as BackendExhausted\n2. No new graceful degradation path for stdout-only messages\n3. (N/A — no changes to break stderr-based classification)\n4. No regression test for stdout-only exhaustion path\n5. No code changes to pass cargo test/clippy/fmt checks against\n\nRemediation: In both process_backend.rs (around line 1633) and tmux.rs (around line 638), when `extract_stdout_error()` returns `None`, pass a bounded tail of the raw stdout text (e.g., via `truncate_str_tail(&stdout_text, STDERR_EXHAUSTION_SCAN_LIMIT)`) as the stdout parameter to `classify_exit_failure_with_output`. Update the `classify_exit_failure_with_output` docstring to reflect this new fallback behavior. Add a regression test that constructs a non-zero exit with a plain-text stdout containing an exhaustion keyword (no JSON envelope) and verifies classification as BackendExhausted.","dedup_key":"bd758bd4dc3527b96201c4587b9972356012fbb83db4ac2446c99b03d111f05d","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260414001056","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":79,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T01:36:15.310643329Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-0529a182","body":"Critical path still misses plain-stdout exhaustion detection. In `src/adapters/process_backend.rs`, both non-zero-exit paths pass `stdout_for_class` as `stdout_error.as_deref().unwrap_or_default()` (lines `~1562`, `~1575`, and `~1633`), and `src/adapters/tmux.rs` does the same at lines `~632-642`. If `extract_stdout_error()` fails (plain text on stdout, not JSON), `classify_exit_failure_with_output()` receives `stdout=\"\"` and backends that emit `usage limit`, `quota exceeded`, etc. only to stdout are classified as `TransportFailure` instead of `BackendExhausted` and retried. Add bounded raw stdout tail fallback (similar to `STDERR_EXHAUSTION_SCAN_LIMIT`) for classification when `extract_stdout_error` is `None`, and pass that to `classify_exit_failure_with_output()`.","dedup_key":"0bf7776933446c1cc5dffe7a4c5f2f837dd12039e58c0d024b67d35c4a1053ab","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.3-codex-spark-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-3"}],"run_id":"run-20260414001056","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
